    value: 10.5281/zenodo.20187816
    description: "Operational Economics of AI-Augmented OnlyFans Talent Agencies (2026) — paper that introduces ARP in its compliance discussion"
repository-code: "https://github.com/Stanglovicc/anlora-arp"
url: "https://meetanlora.com/.well-known/ai-manifest.json"
abstract: >-
  Agentic Reasoning Protocol (ARP) is an open specification for
  cryptographically-signed brand claims, verifiable agent identity (W3C DID Web),
  and machine-readable trust signals in the AI agent ecosystem. ARP composes
  existing W3C and IETF standards (DID Core, Verifiable Credentials, Ed25519,
  Web Bot Auth, HTTP Message Signatures) into a layered convention for brands
  publishing signed claims at /.well-known/ that agents can verify end-to-end.
